columns.name: parameter_group_name
columns.description: The name of the parameter group.

columns.name: allowed_values
columns.description: A range of values within which the parameter can be set.

columns.name: change_type
columns.description: The conditions under which changes to this parameter can be applied. Possible values are 'IMMEDIATE', 'REQUIRES_REBOOT'.

columns.name: data_type
columns.description: The data type of the parameter.

columns.name: is_modifiable
columns.description: Whether the customer is allowed to modify the parameter. Possible values are 'TRUE', 'FALSE' 'CONDITIONAL'.

columns.name: parameter_type
columns.description: Determines whether the parameter can be applied to any node or only nodes of a particular type. Possible values are 'DEFAULT', 'NODE_TYPE_SPECIFIC'.

columns.name: source
columns.description: How the parameter is defined. For example, system denotes a system-defined parameter.
